                  <foliation/>
                  <collation>
                    <p>The quires are at present 11 in number.  What the original signatures of the quires were, does not appear.</p>
                  </collation>
                  <condition>
                    <p>Quires <foreign xml:lang="syr"> ܚ</foreign>,<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܗ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܙ</foreign> , and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܛ</foreign> have been lost, as well as several at the end.</p>
                    <p>Some of the leaves are much stained and torn, especially fol. <locus>1</locus>, <locus>2</locus>, <locus>8</locus>, <locus>28</locus>, <locus>39</locus>, <locus>47</locus>, <locus>48</locus>, <locus>55</locus>, <locus>77</locus>, <locus>78</locus>, <locus>103</locus> and <locus>104</locus>.</p>
                    <p>Leaves are also missing after <locus>foll. 79</locus> and <locus>84</locus></p>
                  </condition>
                </supportDesc>
                <layoutDesc>
                  <layout columns="1" writtenLines="18 21">
                    <p>There are from 18 to 21 lines in each page.</p>
                  </layout>
                </layoutDesc>
              </objectDesc>
              <handDesc>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>The writing is a small, regular Estrangela of the <origDate notBefore="0500" notAfter="0600">vith cent.</origDate></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handnote2" scope="minor" script="syr-Syrj grc" medium="uknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition1 #addition2">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handnote3" scope="minor" script="syr grc" medium="uknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition3">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handnote4" scope="minor" script="syr grc" medium="uknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition4">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
              </handDesc>
              <additions>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                    <p>Numerous Greek vowels have been added by a later hand (<foreign xml:lang="grc">α</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">ε</foreign>, ⲏ, <foreign xml:lang="grc">ω</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὄ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="grc">αυ</foreign>; e.g. <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܘܢܺܬܢܺܐܝܶܠ, ܘܐܘܨܡ, ܘܝܘܐܒ, ܝܬ, ܠܡ̇ܢܘ</foreign>).</p>
                  </item>
   <!-- Missing other vowels on top of these syriac words!!! -->
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                    <p>The same hand that added the vowel-points has divided the books into sections, marked by Greek letters on the margins. The last of these in 1 Chronicles is <foreign xml:lang="grc">ϊθ</foreign> (ch. xxii. 2), fol. <locus>48a</locus>; and in 2 Chronicles (commencing with <foreign xml:lang="grc">Δ</foreign>) ΚΓ (ch. xxix. 1), fol. <locus>104b</locus>.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                    <p>There are also a few marginal notes and glosses; e.g.</p>
                    <p><table><row><cell>fol. <locus from="3a" to="3a">3a</locus>, </cell><cell><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܘܐܺܘܝܡ,</foreign>, </cell><cell>marg.<foreign xml:lang="grc">ηαμ</foreign></cell></row>
                    <row><cell>fol. <locus from="11b" to="11b">11b</locus>, </cell><cell><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܣܩܐ̣</foreign>, </cell><cell>marg.<foreign xml:lang="grc">ⲤⲔⲰ</foreign></cell></row>
                    <row><cell>fol. <locus from="30a" to="30a">30a</locus>, </cell><cell><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܕܩܒܨܝܐܝܠ</foreign>, </cell><cell>marg. <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΚΑΒⲤΗΛ</foreign></cell></row>
                      <row><cell/><cell><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܢܘܠܐ ܕܓܪ̈ܕܚܐ</foreign>, </cell><cell>marg. <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܚܘ̈ܟܶܐ</foreign></cell></row>
                    <row><cell>fol. <locus from="36a" to="36a">36a</locus>, </cell><cell><foreign xml:lang="syr">ܘܕܒ̈ܠܐ. ܘܩܪ̈ܬܠܘܬܐ ܕܥ̈ܢܒܐ</foreign>(<ref target="#b1">1 Chron. xii. 40</ref>),</cell><cell>marg.<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܥ̈ܠܘܗܝ ܕܚܡܪܐ ܐܝܟ ܡܫܠܡܢܘܬܐ ܕܥܒܪ̈ܝܐ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܪ̈ܠܝܬܐ ܕܥ̈ܢܒܐ </foreign></cell></row></table></p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="4" xml:id="addition4">
                    <p>The quires are now signed with letters.</p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
